title: Bannon, Priebus United at CPAC as They Needle Media, Vow to Fulfill Trump Agenda - Fox Nation
text:
Bannon, Priebus United at CPAC as They Needle Media, Vow to Fulfill Trump Agenda Published February 23, 2017 

By GABBY MORRONGIELLO (@GABRIELLAHOPE_) • THE WASHINGTON EXAMINER 
OXON HILL, Md. — Top White House officials Reince Priebus and Steve Bannon urged conservatives on Thursday to ignore reporting about the alleged tensions between them. 
"In regards to us, I think the biggest misconception is everything that you're reading," Priebus, who serves as President Trump's chief of staff, told the crowd gathered for the 44th annual Conservative Political Action Committee Conference. "We are basically together from 6:30 in the morning to 11 o'clock every night." 
In the waning days of Trump's campaign and throughout his first month in office, several media outlets have characterized Priebus and Bannon as enemies vying for the president's attention and for influence in the West Wing. 
Both men pushed back on those claims on Thursday, saying they have used their different backgrounds to collaborate on developing a strong blueprint for the next four years.
